    "Name": "Po II MBT",
    "Details": "A Dark Age variant developed in 3089, this model is protected by Vehicular Stealth Armor powered by an Angel ECM Suite. It carries a Gauss Rifle, twin machine guns and two SRM-6 launchers. While the original Po was intended to be cheap and simple to manufacture and maintain, the modern upgrade traded the Ceres 240 internal combustion engine with a much more expensive but considerably lighter Pitban 240 XL Fusion Engine to allow a great deal increase in firepower. Eleven tons of armor, a modest increase of half a ton, provided average protection for the vehicle's weight.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 4/6 hexes / 120/180 meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Vehicle Stealth Armor\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       235     30\n<b>Left</b>         175     30\n<b>Right</b>       175     30\n<b>Rear</b>        140     30\n<b>Turret</b>      180     30\n\n<b>Total</b>      905    150</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Main Battle Tank</color>",
